S"With the Halifax Mobile Banking app, it\xe2\x80\x99s even easier to manage your Halifax UK personal accounts on the move.Following the release of version 2.0, some customers have reported problems with the app.  \xe2\x80\xa2 Customers updating from a previous version may find the app icon displays incorrectly on the home screen, or disappears. If this happens, please look on your phone\xe2\x80\x99s full app menu to find it.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers having trouble signing in should sign in from their mobile browser by visiting www.halifax.co.uk and selecting Sign in.We apologise for any inconvenience we may have caused. We\xe2\x80\x99re working to release a further update to address these issues as soon as possible.Updates in Version 2.0\xe2\x80\xa2 We\xe2\x80\x99ve seen the feedback, so here\xe2\x80\x99s a little fix to help repair the crashing and connectivity issues that some users have been experiencingNew in Version 1.3\xe2\x80\xa2 Removes minor installation bugBased on your feedback, we\xe2\x80\x99ve made additional improvements to Mobile Banking. Now you can:\xe2\x80\xa2 View your transaction history\xe2\x80\xa2 Register for Online Banking\xe2\x80\xa2 Change some of your personal details\xe2\x80\xa2 Manage your existing overdrafts\xe2\x80\xa2 Switch to the desktop site and backEven if you\xe2\x80\x99re not a Halifax customer, you can still use the app to find Halifax branches and cash machines and LINK ATMs in the UK. If you are a customer but haven\xe2\x80\x99t registered for Online Banking yet, you can do it through your appWith the latest updates, you can now:\xe2\x80\xa2 Find Halifax branches and cash machines, or LINK ATMs in the UK \xe2\x80\xa2 Sign in with your usual Online Banking details\xe2\x80\xa2 View balances and transaction history\xe2\x80\xa2 Check your credit card limit\xe2\x80\xa2 Make transfers between your Halifax UK personal current and savings accounts\xe2\x80\xa2 Set up and make payments \xe2\x80\xa2 Manage your existing overdraft\xe2\x80\xa2 Find useful Halifax phone numbers. And enjoy a high level of security.If you\xe2\x80\x99re already a Halifax personal Online Banking customer, you don\xe2\x80\x99t need to register to use the app\xe2\x80\x99s Mobile Banking services. Simply sign in with your normal Online Banking details wherever you have a signal.Keeping you safe onlineWe try to make sure you\xe2\x80\x99re safe while banking online. We use advanced security technologies and have an online banking guarantee. So you won\xe2\x80\x99t be out-of-pocket even if you're a victim of online fraud.You can help protect yourself too with these simple tips:\xe2\x80\xa2 Always use your mobile device\xe2\x80\x99s security lock or PIN.\xe2\x80\xa2 Switch off Bluetooth unless you\xe2\x80\x99re using it.\xe2\x80\xa2 Be careful about opening MMS attachments, such as picture messages. They can contain viruses.\xe2\x80\xa2 Don\xe2\x80\x99t accept or open any apps or MMS messages from someone you don\xe2\x80\x99t know.\xe2\x80\xa2 Find out what security software might be available from your mobile provider.\xe2\x80\xa2 Treat mobile security as seriously as you treat desktop security.Important information This app and Mobile Banking are designed for use in the UK. We don\xe2\x80\x99t charge you for using this app but your mobile operator may charge for some services. Services may be affected by phone signal and functionality.The Branch/ATM finder uses location based services.  We, LINK Scheme and/or Google may get data about your location (i.e. GPS signals from your mobile device) or data that can be used to approximate your location (such as your mobile ID).The Mobile Banking service in this app is available to our UK personal Online Banking customers only.  Use of it is subject to our Online Banking terms and conditions www.halifax.co.uk/aboutonline/onlineconditions.asp By using this app or providing information to us, you consent to the use and transfer of your information as set out above and in our privacy policy www.halifax.co.uk/securityandprivacy/privacy Halifax is a division of Bank of Scotland plc. This app and Mobile Banking are operated by Bank of Scotland plc (registered in Scotland (No. SC327000) Registered office: The Mound, Edinburgh, EH1 1YZ. Authorised and regulated by the Financial Services Authority.Recent changes:Following the release of version 2.0, some customers have reported problems with the app. \xe2\x80\xa2 Customers updating from a previous version may find the app icon displays incorrectly on the home screen, or disappears. If this happens, please look on your phone\xe2\x80\x99s full app menu to find it\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers having trouble signing in should sign in from their mobile browser by visiting www.halifax.co.ukWe apologise for any inconvenience we may have caused, and are working to release a fix asap."
